</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A61181524A21842266462E251EC7B36" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph id="5B0D5EC286C45BC817E8811091EC61CF" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<pageBreakToken id="046898AAD541CAC6BAB128B619919D30" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3963CF8FC85E66F9CB83D7C2EF7BEA89" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Shrubs, branched, branches glabrous. Leaves oblanceolate, 22-42 mm long, 5-6 mm wide, glabrous, sessile, acute-mucronate, margin entire. Capitula with involucres 18-22 mm high, 12-16 mm wide; phyllaries 6-7-seriate, glabrous, lanceolate, the inner 22-25 mm long, 3-3.5 mm wide, acute, the outer gradually smaller; ray florets 18-20, the corollas 26-28 mm long, the tube 10-11 mm long, glabrous, the outer lip 14-15 mm long, 5-6 mm wide, 4-nerved, tridentate, the inner lip bipartite; disc florets 40-42, the corollas 15-18 mm long, the tube glabrous, the lobes 9-10 mm long, 1-1.2 mm wide, coiled; anthers 6-7 mm long. Achenes [ray] 4-5 mm long, 1.5-1.6 mm wide, glabrous; pappus c. 12 mm long; [disc] 4.5-5 mm long, 1-1.2 mm wide; pappus c. 14 mm long.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7BCF512A730E7AC3F3FEE537F11B281" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5CF905B5BE07F4DC1F9AFF12F1828327" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18A5CE3B4CA4EDDA885E116F24CF919F" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Endemic to an inter-Andean valley in central Peru from near Tarma; c. 3000 m. Given that this species appears confined to a single locality and of a few individuals, it would be considered &quot;critically endangered&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="A6604D38C33D934608FD622C45FEFF05" author="IUCN, Species Survival Commision" journalOrPublisher="Phytologia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="B23" refString="IUCN, Species Survival Commision, 2001. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, United Kingdom, 1-30." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, United Kingdom, 1 - 30." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EEE159E3438F4D6C969391DAD5CDD148" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion.">
<paragraph id="9AED905D018A1175EAA8BC3BA99E2DEB" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="97E1830E4D4B18EBA33BA6A64C6969F0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="F80D472276F7A44CE87B273A700DCE41" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis id="895AD7D7C66DB888B8F10EE7FDDBEF63" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Plazia conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare species, and type material has not been located. No new material had been collected since Ruiz 
<normalizedToken id="4F28757CDAF0E3A3C9729EE11F14C5E2" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="E6232405F82357B39259A6C55BC69E9E" originalValue="Pavón’s">Pavon's</normalizedToken>
original gathering until a second collection was made by Felix Woytkowski at the type locality nearly 180 years after its original description. 
<bibRefCitation id="59EB6A235A5FD84E7C75774B4E6B0BAA" author="Cabrera, AL" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="195 - 215" refId="B2" refString="Cabrera, AL, 1960. Notas sobre tipos de Compuestas Sudamericanas en herbarios Europeos. III, Los tipos de Ruiz y Pavon. Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 8 (3-4): 195 - 215" title="Notas sobre tipos de Compuestas Sudamericanas en herbarios Europeos. III, Los tipos de Ruiz y Pavon." volume="8" year="1960">Cabrera (1960)</bibRefCitation>
was unsuccessful in locating Ruiz 
<normalizedToken id="DDE137042E9A56A4D10F45723D3364E3" originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="1619813ECE803B34C2A7CE2E5B0DEF57" originalValue="Pavón’s">Pavon's</normalizedToken>
type material in the major European herbaria, including Madrid. We made inquiries to the Real 
<normalizedToken id="C1403E7A5F21C0DB49E59589226D1B08" originalValue="Jardín">Jardin</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="49765E2CACF58C8550BFD2F598AC4AEE" originalValue="Botánico">Botanico</normalizedToken>
in Madrid, but no collection of 
<taxonomicName id="F319BF20E9FF656BADC7665A67235F27" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Plazia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A40DE4C6236D2ECD7D6EAD698AB267B1" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Plazia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has surfaced as yet. 
<bibRefCitation id="FB11B16AC7E3F4A0DF9C956B3754A42F" author="Ferreyra, R" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Peruana de Botanica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="101 - 105" refId="B6" refString="Ferreyra, R, 1980. El genero Plazia en el Peru. Boletin de la Sociedad Peruana de Botanica 8: 101 - 105" title="El genero Plazia en el Peru." volume="8" year="1980">Ferreyra (1980)</bibRefCitation>
cited duplicates of 
<emphasis id="5BBEBCCE5264A5CA22ED01BADB372589" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Woytkowski 52</emphasis>
as occurring at MO and F, but after exhaustive searching, no duplicate collections were located, and subsequently the duplicates were not cited in 
<normalizedToken id="B2D5715587C44E006E62FB6B6B64D9C8" originalValue="Ferreyra’s">Ferreyra's</normalizedToken>
Flora of Peru treatment (1995). Further, during this study, we were unsuccessful in our efforts to examine the Woytkowski collection at USM, and the description provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="AB26AA8B4C2A456A02B140D50A4301DC" author="Ferreyra, R" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Peruana de Botanica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="B7" refString="Ferreyra, R, 1995. Family Asteraceae: Part VI, Tribe Mutiseae. In: MacbrideJF et al. Flora of Peru. Fieldiana Botany. N.S.35: 1-101." title="Family Asteraceae: Part VI, Tribe Mutiseae. In: MacbrideJF et al. Flora of Peru. Fieldiana Botany. N. S. 35: 1 - 101." year="1995">Ferreyra (1995)</bibRefCitation>
was used to quantify the differences between that species and the new one described here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03C8F24CE18F286E8795B2189EDD7166" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
There is an error in the citation of the generic description in Florae Peruvianae Chilensis Prodromus (1794), where page 
<normalizedToken id="AB75481583AA02B25754A03DCA90B67F" originalValue="“104”">&quot;104&quot;</normalizedToken>
is cited in Systema Vegetabilium Florae Peruvianae et Chilensis (1798) incorrectly, and the generic description is actually on page 92.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
